"""
To be used on SQLite database files

python getInsertStatements.py -i name_of_file.db3

Example:

python getInsertStatements.py -i 8thAndAdams.db3

This will create a new database using the name of the file as the name of the database. Please ensure you do not use a file name that already exists in your MySQL instance. At the moment, if this happens the script will produce an error, but if you wish it can be extended to drop the database if it already exists. But if a client were to use this, they may delete databases unknowingly.


"""



